Hi Kaitlin,
Would you be able to help me with something?
Attached is a list of contacts that were pulled from Scoro.
**Please jus look at the tab "Nicole."
The ask is for you to delete the contacts from this list that have a comment similar to "email didn't go through - Update Scoro" or "No longer at company."
Are you able to delete those contacts from Scoro? In some cases, my guess is that it won't let you, should that person be associated with something, like a Quote. Also, you may not have permission to do this. If you don't, lmk, and I'll change your permissions.
Could you please give it a try & see if you can delete them? You can see my notes in Column O. I started highlighting the people in red, but then I stopped  🙂. Column O will indicate whether they should be removed.
If this can be done by this Friday that would be great. If not, just lmk when you think you can get done.
Happy to also hop on a call if needed to help.
Thank you!

subject: Feb.11 webinar update
body:
Hi & Thanks for all of your help this week!
Just wanted to update you that we have made the Feb.11th webinar live. People have been getting emails to sign up, and we've gotten about 20 people signed up so far!
What I'll need from you is your brain in figuring out the best way to send these people the Zoom link.
We had people sign up in HubSpot so we could capture a lot of data.
What I'm wondering now is, what's next?
I can download the registered people as a list I can share with you.
Is it best we simply send them a calendar invite from Outlook.... (not sure if we can Bcc)... OR is it better to have you manually register them in Zoom so they get an email with the Zoom link & then then can choose to add it to their calendar... OR ...???
I'll schedule a time for us on Monday to chat through this. If you can come up with ideas for how best to approach it prior to our call, that would be great. LMK if you have any questions in the meantime.
Thanks!!
Nicole Barile
